public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    try {
      throw new IllegalArgumentException("This is an unchecked exception");
    } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
      System.out.println("Exception caught: " + e.getMessage());
    }
  }
}





3 c-Write a program to throw an checked exception explicitly using 'throw' keyword and Don't either handle or use the throws clause.  

class ExceptionThrown {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        throw new java.io.IOException("Exception thrown explicitly.");
    }
}




4-	Write a program in which main method calls the foo method which calls the bar method. Bar method can throw a checked exception. Use throws for throwing the exception from bar. Don’t handle exception in bar using try catch. Let the calling function handle the same.  

class Main {
   public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
      foo();
   }

   static void foo() throws InterruptedException {
      bar();
   }

   static void bar() throws InterruptedException {
      throw new InterruptedException("This is a checked exception.");
   }
}



5.	6.	Create a User defined exception – LoanNotApprovedException. In case the given criteria of Loan approval doesn’t match, the exception must be thrown. The Loan Approval criterions for different type of loans are available in Eligibility.txt file. The exception should specifically give details about the mismatched criteria because of which the loan could not be approved.   


import java.io.IOException;

class LoanNotApprovedException extends Exception {
   String message;

   LoanNotApprovedException(String message) {
      this.message = message;
   }

   public String getMessage() {
      return message;
   }
}

class Loan {
   void checkEligibility(String criteria) throws LoanNotApprovedException {
      try {
         // Read criteria from "Eligibility.txt" file
         // ...
         if (!criteria.equals("Eligible")) {
            throw new LoanNotApprovedException("Loan not approved due to mismatched criteria: " + criteria);
         }
      } catch (IOException e) {
         System.out.println("Error reading eligibility criteria from file.");
      }
   }
}

class Main {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      Loan loan = new Loan();
      try {
         loan.checkEligibility("Ineligible");
      } catch (LoanNotApprovedException e) {
         System.out.println(e.getMessage());
      }
   }
}
